article.headline: Cornell 68, Dartmouth 59
article.story: HANOVER, N.H. -- Shonn Miller had his second career double-double with 15 points and 10 rebounds, and Cornell kept Dartmouth winless in Ivy League play with a 68-59 win on Saturday night. Chris Wroblewski finished with 14 points and Johnathan Gray added 13 for the Big Red (8-12, 3-3), who scored the first 10 points of the game and never trailed. Cornell held the Big Green (4-18, 0-6) to 35 percent shooting (19 of 54) from the floor and 3 of 17 from beyond the arc. Miller, who also had three steals, helped Cornell force Dartmouth into 15 turnovers. Dartmouth cut the Big Red's lead to two points with 1:42 remaining in the game. But the Big Green pulled no closer, as Cornell closed the game with a 9-2 run to pull away. Kirk Crecco led Dartmouth with 15 points. Gabas Maldunas had 10 points, five rebounds and three blocks.
